    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go to the List of Blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <em>Buttons block </em>to add one or more buttons to your page or post. This block has been available since WordPress 5.4, when the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/button-block/\"><em>button block</em></a> was deprecated.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"407\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1024x407.png\" alt=\"Buttons block on the editor canvas\" class=\"wp-image-16359224\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1024x407.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-300x119.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-768x305.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1536x611.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-2048x815.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add the <em>Buttons </em>block to a page, click the<strong> Add block</strong> button to open the block inserter pop-up window and choose the <em>Buttons</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1424\" height=\"596\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/adding-a-buttons-block.gif\" alt=\"A demo of adding a buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355793\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use the keyboard shortcut <kbd>/buttons</kbd> to quickly insert a <em>Buttons</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Buttons block</em> comes with one individual button block by default. You can customize the text, link, and style for this button. To add more buttons, click the plus <strong>Add block</strong> button in the bottom right corner within the <em>Buttons block</em>, and a new button will appear. Note that the new button will follow the same style as the existing button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"676\" height=\"238\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/adding-a-button.gif\" alt=\"A demo of adding a button inside the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355794\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:41px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-toolbar-for-entire-block\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To view the block toolbar, click on the block, and the toolbar will be displayed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block comes with unique toolbar icons and blocks specific user controls that allow you to manipulate the block right in the editor.The <em>Buttons</em> block has a toolbar for the individual button and a toolbar for the entire block.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">For the entire block</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"592\" height=\"112\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/buttons-toolbar.png\" alt=\"Buttons block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16355795\" style=\"object-fit:cover\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/buttons-toolbar.png 592w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/buttons-toolbar-300x57.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 592px) 100vw, 592px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The main toolbar for the entire block has the following buttons:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Drag icon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Move arrows</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change items justification</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change vertical alignment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Transform to </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"662\" height=\"388\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform.png\" alt=\"&quot;Transform to&quot; option for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355796\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform.png 662w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-300x176.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the \u201cTransform\u201d button to convert the <em>Buttons</em> block into a \u201cGroup\u201d or \u201cColumns\u201d block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Drag icon</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"584\" height=\"112\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/moving-drag.png\" alt=\"Drag icon to move the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355797\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/moving-drag.png 584w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/moving-drag-300x58.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 584px) 100vw, 584px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To drag and drop the block to a new location on the page template, click and hold the rectangle of dots, then drag it to the new location. The blue separator line indicates where the block will be placed. Release the left mouse button when you find the new location to place the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Move arrows</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"586\" height=\"116\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/moving-arrows.png\" alt=\"Arrow icons to move the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355798\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/moving-arrows.png 586w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/moving-arrows-300x59.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 586px) 100vw, 586px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The up and down arrow icons can be used to move the block up and down on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/moving-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\">Get more information about moving a block within the editor.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change items justification</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"658\" height=\"464\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/justify.png\" alt=\"Horizontal justification settings for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355799\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/justify.png 658w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/justify-300x212.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The items justification setting allows justifying the buttons to the left, center, or right. There is also an option to \u201cSpace between items\u201d. If it is selected, the <em>Buttons</em><strong><em> </em></strong>block will be centered with equal spacing between the buttons.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1328\" height=\"252\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/space-between-items.png\" alt=\"Buttons block with space between items alignment\" class=\"wp-image-16355800\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/space-between-items.png 1328w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/space-between-items-300x57.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/space-between-items-1024x194.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/space-between-items-768x146.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1328px) 100vw, 1328px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change vertical alignment</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"598\" height=\"453\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/vertical-alignment.png\" alt=\"Vertical alignment settings for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355801\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/vertical-alignment.png 598w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/vertical-alignment-300x227.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 598px) 100vw, 598px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the change vertical alignment option to align buttons vertically with four possible options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Align top</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align middle</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align bottom</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stretch to fill&nbsp;</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Align</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"856\" height=\"420\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-toolbar.png\" alt=\"Block alignment options for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355802\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-toolbar.png 856w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-toolbar-300x147.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-toolbar-768x377.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 856px) 100vw, 856px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the change alignment tool to align the <em>Buttons </em>block. Choose one of the following options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>None \u2013 </strong>leaves the block the current size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wide width \u2013 </strong>increase the width of the block beyond the content size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Full width \u2013 </strong>extend the block to cover the full width of the screen.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The \u201cWide width\u201d and \u201cFull width\u201d alignment settings must be enabled by your WordPress theme.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Options</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Options button on a block toolbar gives you more features to customize the block.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1350\" height=\"1042\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/options-menu.png\" alt=\"Options menu for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355803\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/options-menu.png 1350w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/options-menu-300x232.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/options-menu-1024x790.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/options-menu-768x593.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1350px) 100vw, 1350px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/more-options/\" target=\"_blank\">Get more information about other settings</a></p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:41px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">For individual button</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"880\" height=\"237\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-2.png\" alt=\"Individual button block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16359227\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-2.png 880w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-2-300x81.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-2-768x207.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 880px) 100vw, 880px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you select a specific button, a new toolbar will appear with these new options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Change block style</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Link</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bold</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Italic</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More Rich Text controls</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change block style</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"884\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-3.png\" alt=\"Change block styles for individual block\" class=\"wp-image-16359228\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-3.png 884w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-3-300x106.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-3-768x270.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 884px) 100vw, 884px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the change block style option to change the style of a particular button.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Link</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"697\" height=\"70\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/image-1.png\" alt=\"Link settings in the button block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16355813\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/image-1.png 697w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/image-1-300x30.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 697px) 100vw, 697px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the link option to add a link to the button. It\u2019s also possible to set it to open the link in a new tab</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bold</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"94\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-5.png\" alt=\"Bold text format in the button block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16359230\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-5.png 850w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-5-300x33.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-5-768x85.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can select the text in the <em>Buttons</em> block and use the \u201cBold\u201d option or \u201cCtrl+B\u201d / \u201cCmd+B\u201d on your keyboard to bold it, which is usually heavier than the surrounding text.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Italic</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"850\" height=\"94\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-6.png\" alt=\"Italic text format in the button block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16359231\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-6.png 850w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-6-300x33.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-6-768x85.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can select the text in the <em>Buttons</em> block and use the \u201cItalic\u201d option or \u201cCtrl+I\u201d / \u201cCmd+I\u201d on your keyboard to italicize it, which usually appears slanted to the right.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>More rich text options</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The drop-down menu to the left of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">More options menu</a>&nbsp;contains a range of additional rich text editing options such as highlighting, inline code, strikethrough, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-text-editing-overview/\">Read about more rich text editing options.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Options</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1023\" height=\"829\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1.png\" alt=\"The options button on the block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16359226\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1.png 1023w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1-300x243.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-1-768x622.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1023px) 100vw, 1023px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Options button on a block toolbar gives you more features to customize a specific button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:41px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-settings-for-entire-block\">Block settings </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The block settings panel contains customization options specific to the block. To open it, select the block and click the <strong>Settings </strong>button next to the <strong>Publish </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"758\" height=\"144\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-7.png\" alt=\"The settings button at the top right corner of editor\" class=\"wp-image-16359232\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-7.png 758w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-7-300x57.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When the entire <em>Buttons</em> block is selected, you have the Layout, Typography, Dimensions, and Advanced customization settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-settings-for-entire-block\">For the entire block</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When the entire <em>buttons block</em> is selected, you have the Layout, Dimensions, and Advanced settings for customization.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Layout</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Buttons</em> block provides layout settings to change item justification and orientation.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"486\" height=\"279\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/image.png\" alt=\"Layout settings for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16355811\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/image.png 486w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/image-300x172.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 486px) 100vw, 486px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When a specific button from the <em>Buttons</em> block is selected, you have the Styles, Width, Color, Typography, Dimensions, Border, and Advanced customization settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/layout-settings-overview/\">This article provides details about layout settings.</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Color</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Buttons</em> block provides Color settings options to change the text and background colors</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"946\" height=\"759\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-8.png\" alt=\"Color settings for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16359233\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-8.png 946w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-8-300x241.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-8-768x616.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 946px) 100vw, 946px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"> <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">See this guide for more information about changing colors.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Typography</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Buttons</em> block<em> </em>provides typography settings to change the font family, size, appearance, line height, letter case, letter spacing, and decoration.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Get more details about changing typography settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dimensions</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Buttons</em> block provides dimensions settings options to change padding and margin size.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Learn more about dimension controls.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Border</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Border settings provide options to control the width and radius on each side of the button. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"473\" height=\"321\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-9.png\" alt=\"Border settings for the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-16359234\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-9.png 473w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/11/image-9-300x204.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 473px) 100vw, 473px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Learn more about border settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">For individual button</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Styles settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s possible to change the individual button style. Hover over a particular style to see how it looks.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"755\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/button-styles-panel-1024x755.png\" alt=\"Styles settings for the individual button block\" class=\"wp-image-16355815\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/button-styles-panel-1024x755.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/button-styles-panel-300x221.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/button-styles-panel-768x567.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/button-styles-panel.png 1052w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Width settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"524\" height=\"152\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-settings.png\" alt=\"Width settings for the individual button block\" class=\"wp-image-16355814\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-settings.png 524w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/width-settings-300x87.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Each button can have its own width setting inside the <em>buttons block</em> based on a % value.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Advanced settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"268\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/10/buttons-block-sidebar-advanced.png\" alt=\"Advanced settings for the individual button in the buttons block\" class=\"wp-image-14957600\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/10/buttons-block-sidebar-advanced.png 268w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/10/buttons-block-sidebar-advanced-189x300.png 189w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 268px) 100vw, 268px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add a <strong>Link rel</strong> attribute to each button in the block. This is a more advanced feature that enables to control the button link\u2019s&nbsp;<code>rel</code>&nbsp;attribute, The <kbd>rel</kbd> attribute defines the relationship between a linked resource and the button. Eg: for rel attributes are&nbsp;<code>nofollow</code>, <kbd>external</kbd>, <kbd>stylesheet</kbd>, <kbd>pingback</kbd>, <kbd>preload</kbd>, <kbd>prefetch</kbd>, <kbd>prev</kbd>&nbsp;etc</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add HTML anchor and CSS class(es) to each button in the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HTML anchor</strong> allows you to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/page-jumps/\">make a unique web address</a>&nbsp;for an individual button. Then, you\u2019ll be able to link directly to that button on your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Additional CSS class(es)</strong> lets you add CSS class(es) to your button, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the button as you see fit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on which style you choose for the button block, WordPress automatically adds a CSS class to that button block. You can find the class in the Advanced settings panel under Additional CSS class(es). You can also add additional classes with spaces.</p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-large-font-size\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-11-21\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated screenshots for 6.4</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-11-11\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated title in sentence case </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-06-09\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Replaced &#8220;More rich text options&#8221; section with short summary linking to new dedicated page for rich text editing options.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-03-07\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Revised formatting for the whole article</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated content and all screenshots for 6.2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-11-22\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Change alignment for images </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replaced redundant content</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-08-18\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated content, screenshots, and videos for 6.0.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added explanation for adding individual buttons and style preservation.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added new block toolbar options.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added images and info for space between items and change vertical alignment.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added details for the block settings sidebar info.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated info for the More options for the individual button block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Removed Text Color from the block toolbar for the individual button block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added ALT tags for the images.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-02-15\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated screenshots to 5.9</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated video to 5.9</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added new settings for previous versions</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added Live example</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
